\f1\b NOTES FOR MACINTOSH USERS
\f0\b0 \
\
\

\f1\b For The Record
\f0\b0 \
\
I am not the developer of SyncTERM. I am merely a casual\
user of SyncTERM who has helped the developer, Stephen Hurd,\
by reporting bugs and problems, which have helped him to\
make SyncTERM more compatible with the Macintosh platform. I\
wrote this help file to assist new Macintosh users of\
SyncTERM in using the program. While SyncTERM does not\
currently have a beautiful Macintosh interface,\
nevertheless, functionality-wise, it is very good. In fact,\
to my knowledge, none of the "pretty boy" Macintosh telnet\
clients display BBS ANSI graphics as well as SyncTERM does.\
\
\

