\f1\b How To Enter A New BBS Entry
\f0\b0 \
\

\f1\b 1
\f0\b0 . If your keyboard does not have an "insert" key, hit\
either the "help" key, or else the modifier combination\
shift-/=. In other words, hold down the "shift" key while\
you simultaneously hit the +/= key. Another way is to simply\
click on the very bottom of the BBS directory, below the\
last BBS entry. This will bring up a new blank field.\
\

\f1\b 2
\f0\b0 . Enter the BBS name and hit the "return" key.\
\

\f1\b 3
\f0\b0 . In the "Connection Type" window, use the arrow keys to\
make your selection, and then hit the "return" key. You will\
normally want to choose "Telnet".\
\

\f1\b 4
\f0\b0 . Enter the domain name or IP address for the BBS and hit\
the "return" key.\
\
\

\f1\b How To Remove A BBS Entry
\f0\b0 \
\
After selecting the BBS name in the BBS Directory list, hit the\
"del" key which is located just below the "help" key, and to the\
left of the "end" key. Do NOT hit the "delete" key as this will\
entirely quit SyncTERM.\
\
\

\f1\b How To Edit A BBS Entry
\f0\b0 \
\
Use the arrow keys to select the entry in the BBS Directory\
and hit the F2 function key.\
\
\

\f1\b How To Connect To A BBS
\f0\b0 \
\
Simple click on a BBS entry in the BBS Directory list and\
the connection will initiate.\
\
\

\f1\b How To Bring Up SyncTERM Menu
\f0\b0 \
\
Use the key combination Command-Z (if ALT-Z doesn't work for\
you).\
\
\

\f1\b How To Enable And Use Scrollback
\f0\b0 \
\

\f1\b 1
\f0\b0 . Use the key combination Command-B (if ALT-B doesn't work\
for you).\
\

\f1\b 2
\f0\b0 . Use the "page up" and "page down" keys to scroll back one\
full screen.\
\

\f1\b 3
\f0\b0 . Use the "up" and "down" arrow keys to scroll one line at\
a time.\
\

\f1\b 4
\f0\b0 . Hit the "esc" key to deactivate scrollback mode.\
\
\

